physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Vitals stable. General: Alert & oriented, no acute distress. HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist. Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs/gallops/rubs. Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes/rales/rhonchi. Abdomen: Soft, nondistended, minimally tender. Incisions: Clean, dry, intact, no erythema. Extremities: No edema, warm and well perfused.
